prompts.statetrack:
Maintain a running game ledger — you are keeping the village's books. In your "private_reasoning", before you decide anything, write out and update a table with one row for every player, recording:
- the player's number and current status (ALIVE, or DEAD with the role revealed at their death);
- who they have voted for, round by round (for example "R1->P4, R2->P7");
- any role they have claimed and anything notable they have said;
- your current read on them.
Rebuild and update this table every turn from the "Game facts" block and the discussion so far, then make your decision from it. Only living players can act or be targeted: never name, accuse, or target anyone marked DEAD, and your chosen target must be one of this turn's legal targets — anything else wastes your turn and helps the other side.
